article.headline: Eagles' 15-0 run in second half seals win
article.linkText: Deveny's 24 points leads BC past Colorado State
article.story:
CHESTNUT HILL, Mass. (Ticker) -- Jessalyn Deveny 
scored a game-high 24 points and Becky Gottstein added 17 to
lead No. 24 Boston College past Colorado State 75-60.

Deveny and Gottstein combined to score all of the Eagles' points
during a 15-0 run at the start of the second half.  Deveny had
16 points in the second half while Gottstein added 15.

Boston College (10-3, 3-0) outscored the Rams (8-5), 30-16, in
the paint, shot 47 percent from the floor and hit 19 of its 22
free throws.

Ashely Augspurger had 13 points and Shannon Strecker came off
the bench and added 12 for Colorado St., which had its four-game
winning streak snapped.

The Rams went just 5-for-22 from beyond the 3-point arc.
